from directed_graphs.backwards import BackwardsNode2Vec
from torch_geometric.utils import to_networkx

G_nx = to_networkx(data, to_undirected=False)
node2vec2_model = BackwardsNode2Vec(G_nx, backward_discount=0.2, p=10, q=0.5, dimensions=3, walk_length=20, num_walks=5000, workers=4)
emb = node2vec2_model.get_embeddings(window=1)

num_randwalks = 10
q_values = [1, 2]
length_walks = [5, 10, 20]
dimension_d = [16, 32, 64]
context_size = [5, 10]
backward_discounts = [0.2, 0.5]
images = []

for context in context_size:
    for q_value in q_values:
        for length_walk in length_walks:
            for backward_discount in backward_discounts:
                node2vec2_model = BackwardsNode2Vec(G_nx, backward_discount=backward_discount, p=1, q=q_value, dimensions=32, walk_length=length_walk, num_walks=num_randwalks, workers=4)
                emb = node2vec2_model.get_embeddings(window=context)
                images.append(plot_embeddings(emb, num_nodes=data.num_nodes, num_clusters=7))
